V<<stats>>\u000a\u000a"Good as can be when there are shades crawling out of every knothole," Mem responds grimly. You feel your smile falter. The twisting in your belly tells you what Mem's getting at, but you can only stare as she continues.\u000a\u000a"We had a deal," she tells you, gripping her axe handle with callused hands. "You keep the shades off my property and I let you stick around in that old cottage for free. Or are you too lazy to get more than one or two jellies a month?"\u000a\u000aYou feel your cheeks burning red but you somehow manage to keep the old woman's gaze. This seems to make an impression on her and she sighs, loosening her grip on her axe. When she speaks again, her voice is slightly kinder.\u000a\u000a"I do appreciate all you've done for my family so far, which is why I'm going to sweeten the deal for you. From now on, I'll pay you a bounty. Every shade you kill, I give you a prime log for your fire. Will that help?"\u000a\u000a[["Yes. Thanks."|S1 Reply to Mem 1b]]
