V<<stats>>\u000a\u000a"Well. I better go," you say, standing. Kerim nods and raises a hand in parting. You grab your spear and shield and step out of the inn and into the cool night.\u000a\u000aParrier's Rest is a fishing town, and a small one at that. Most of its inhabitants live off the sea, or by providing goods to sailors on leave. Tonight, as on most nights, the townsfolk have gone to bed early. Few windows along the shore are still lit. The wharf is utterly deserted, the only sounds from the sea and the boats, the ropes and the dock itself.\u000a\u000aBehind you, Kerim locks the inn for the evening. A sudden melancholy overtakes you.\u000a\u000a<span class="nonchoice">Go home</span>\u000a[[Linger at the dock|S1 Linger at the dock]]
